 what they felt and understood about their experience. An accessible and captivating reading, this volume presents a close-up, human size dimension of the destruction. The books written by child survivors also describe the resources and means that helped them to remain human even in the deepest well of inhumanity, offering precious lessons about resistance and resilience.M  afunded by Opening the Future  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aChildrenxCrimes against. 0aChildren's writings. 0aGenocide survivors. 0aHolocaust survivors' writings. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Genocide & War Crimes.2bisacsh  aBosnia.  aCambodia.  aHolocaust.  aRwanda.  agenocide.  aresilience.  aresistance.  asurvival.2 aOpening the Futureefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCentral European University Press eBook-Package 2023z978311079759608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2023 Englishz978311131925408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2023z9783111318677oZDB-23-PLW40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789633866191?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789633866191zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789633866191/original  a978-3-11-079759-6 Central European University Press eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131925-4 EBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2023 Englishb2023  